{
  "text": "Ignoring this additional correlation, also causes the correlation between the hurdle and the count process to be lower than 1, in absolute value, and that is true even if u i and \u03b5 i have full correlation, since the variation in y i does not only result from the variations in the unobserved heterogeneity term. [CITATION_1] ignores this second source of correlation.",
  "citation_candidates": [
